pip install sentence-transformers nltk

Tunable Options
threshold: raises/lower to get stricter or broader synonym matches.


⚙️ Optional Tweaks
Increase top_n in kw_model.extract_keywords() to include more phrases per document.
Raise THRESHOLD (e.g. 0.75) for tighter semantic groups.
Use a stronger model like "all-mpnet-base-v2" for more accuracy on complex topics.

project/
│
├── generate_synonyms.py
├── texts/
│   ├── geography.txt
│   ├── environment.txt
│   └── hydrology.txt
└── synonyms.txt

torch is required by Sentence Transformers — version ≥ 2.3.0 recommended.
scikit-learn is used internally by KeyBERT.
These versions are tested and compatible as of late 2025.

# spatial = geospatial:87+geographic:83+terrestrial:79
# land use = land cover:81+land characterization:78+land surface:75+ownership property:73
# wetlands = wet land:72+nwi:70+hydric soil:69+inundated:67
# hydrography = stream:85+river:83+spring:81+lake:78+pond:75+aqueduct:72+siphon:70+well:68
# hypsography = elevation:82+relief:79+topography:77+contour:73

weight = int(similarity * 100) gives an intuitive 0–100 scale.
You can raise THRESHOLD (e.g. 0.7–0.8) for more confident synonyms.
Multiword phrases are handled automatically.
The file synonyms.txt is safe to parse later for indexing or search enrichment.
